    <div><b><A class="WebOption" HREF="/HousePublications/GetWebOptionsCallBack.aspx?SourceSystem=PRISM&amp;ResourceType=Affiliation&amp;ResourceID=128843&amp;language=1&amp;DisplayMode=2">Mr. Ted Menzies (Parliamentary Secretary to the Minister of Finance, CPC)</A>: </b>&nbsp;<span class="nextIntervention"><a class="nav_link" href="#Int-2658817"><img src="/common/images/arrow2_right.gif" border="0" alt="next intervention"></a></span></div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Speaker, as a matter of fact, the government actually may have an economic action plan that it can now put into place. We are happy that the senators have decided to move on.</div>
