  <div>
    <div><b><A class="WebOption" HREF="/HousePublications/GetWebOptionsCallBack.aspx?SourceSystem=PRISM&amp;ResourceType=Affiliation&amp;ResourceID=128675&amp;language=1&amp;DisplayMode=2">Hon. Gerry Byrne (Humber—St. Barbe—Baie Verte, Lib.)</A>: </b><span class="nextIntervention"><a class="nav_link" href="#Int-2658955"><img src="/common/images/arrow2_left.gif" border="0" alt="previous intervention"></a></span>&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Speaker, that is very funny because in the proposed act the minister says that there should be no avenue for appeal. She was absolutely adamant about that, as was the previous minister. </div>
</p><a name="Para1341617" xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt"></a><p xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt">
  <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The people who are being hurt here are the 28,000 commercial fishermen and plant workers in Atlantic Canada who now have a minister who is prepared to sacrifice conservation and proper stewardship of the resource for the sake of a political gift before the last election campaign.</div>
</p><a name="Para1341618" xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt"></a><p xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt">
  <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The industry is facing unparalleled crises in terms of access to capital and access to resources, but as well, reduced markets. Will there be a full inquiry about this particular move, yes or no?</div>
</p><A NAME="Int-2658962"></A><a HREF="#Int-2658964"><IMG SRC="/common/images/arrow2_down.gif" border="0" alt="next intervention"></a>&nbsp;<a HREF="#Int-2658960"><IMG SRC="/common/images/arrow2_up.gif" border="0" alt="previous intervention"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
