        <a name="Para1341749" xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt"></a><p xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt">
  <div>
    <div><b><A class="WebOption" HREF="/HousePublications/GetWebOptionsCallBack.aspx?SourceSystem=PRISM&amp;ResourceType=Affiliation&amp;ResourceID=128784&amp;language=1&amp;DisplayMode=2">Hon. Larry Bagnell (Yukon, Lib.)</A>: </b><span class="nextIntervention"><a class="nav_link" href="#Int-2659094"><img src="/common/images/arrow2_left.gif" border="0" alt="previous intervention"></a></span>&nbsp;<span class="nextIntervention"><a class="nav_link" href="#Int-2659331"><img src="/common/images/arrow2_right.gif" border="0" alt="next intervention"></a></span></div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Speaker, on a point of order, during question period the <A class="WebOption" HREF="/HousePublications/GetWebOptionsCallBack.aspx?SourceSystem=PRISM&amp;ResourceType=Affiliation&amp;ResourceID=128843&amp;language=1&amp;DisplayMode=2">Parliamentary Secretary to the Minister of Finance</A> suggested that no Liberals had given input on the budget at the request of the finance minister. I would not raise this except it has been said a number of times before. </div>
